# Symfony Package Coding Standards

- File names: Use PascalCase (e.g., MyClassFile.php)
- Class and Enum names: Use PascalCase (e.g., MyClass)
- Method names: Use camelCase (e.g., myMethod)
- Variable and Properties names: Use camelCase (e.g., myVariable)
- Constants names: Use SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., MY_CONSTANT)
- Enum Cases names: Use SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., MY_CASE)
- Constructor Property Promotion: Always use constructor property promotion when possible
- Enums: Prefer using enums over multiple constants for representing a fixed set of values
- Immutability: Use readonly properties when possible and make DTOs immutable